    <text id="F8006T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McPherson comments on President Buchanan's record and on his own business.</p>
            </div1>
            <div1 type="envelope" id="d4">
                <p><abbr expan="Edward">E.</abbr> McPherson<lb/><abbr expan="December">Dec</abbr>
                    14, 1858</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d5">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d6">
             

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1858-12-14"><abbr expan="December">Dec.</abbr> 14, 58</date>
                        <name type="place">Gettysburg,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your sending a check of $20 for one Band, has been <abbr expan="received">rec<hi
                            rend="underline">d</hi></abbr>.- I'm <unclear>sure</unclear> men will be
                    delighted to hear of your contribution, for they are anxious to purchase the
                    instruments, &amp; have encountered many obstacles.- They will accept this
                    gratefully, as renewed evidence of your liberality &amp; your interest in
                    the cause which so <unclear>namely</unclear> enlists their sympathies. The
                        <unclear>horns</unclear> are to be held by the <unclear>com
                    &amp;c</unclear> named, &amp; we hope the Band will have a prosperous
                    future.-- It will be a help, in our contests for the primary in this county.</p>
                <p>I did not know until the other day, that the gentlemen had written <unclear>it
                    on</unclear> (for I have been much from home) &amp; <unclear>if I</unclear>
                    can find something to occupy me, I will <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> the <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> in
                        <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> probably; but I can't "loaf" all that time. My nature
                        <unclear>relates</unclear> I am happiest when busiest.<pb n="3"/>I
                    understand how numerous must be the caller upon you.</p>
                <p>I do not expect to reach Washington until <abbr expan="January">Jan</abbr>
                    4-probably about the middle.- I wish to be <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>
                    <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> at the opening, to serve <unclear>especially</unclear> a very
                    deserving county man, John Picking, <unclear>Viz.</unclear>, who is a candidate
                    for <unclear>transcribing</unclear> clerk. <unclear>I doubt</unclear> there are
                    a legion of candidates.</p>
                <p>There should be a committee of <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> raised to examine into Buchanan's
                    case.--On <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>
                    <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> in disgracing the State.--All true State men Should write to
                    make a better Pennsylvanian the next <abbr expan="President">Pres<hi
                            rend="underline">t</hi></abbr>, if for no other reason, to show the
                    nation that our people are not all bereft of Common Sense.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours truly</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline"><abbr expan="Edward">Edwd.</abbr> McPherson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
